attributes.Long form description: The student wants to assemble a rashult. First, he assembles the side half frames to each other, then the student assembles the base frame of the furniture together with the side frames and screws everything up. Now, the student takes the bottom grid tray and inserts it into the base frame of the rashult. Next, the student grabs the brackets from the utility cart and screws them to the bottom grid tray. Then, the student takes the remaining grid trays and inserts them into the utility cart. He rotates the rashult downwards the table and aligns the grid trays to their slots. Using the brackets and the hexagonal wrench, the student, screws the top and the middle grid trays to the rashult with the remaining brackets. Finally, the student rotates the rashult and screws the four legs to the furniture.
